<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0591 </DOCNO><TEXT>The vasculation of the middle ear and its diagnostic value in high resolutioncomputer tomography has been described in the literature. An analysisof the capillaries of a middle ear hemangioma is presented here, to ourknowledge, for the first time. In addition to this description, otherpathological processes of middle ear disease, such as effusion, cholesteatoma,sclerosis of the tympanic membrane, as well as primary carcinoma or sarcomatousdisease and also metastases are considered in differential diagnosis.</TEXT></DOC>